metadata.name: Prime Time #1/35
metadata.description: Manhattan as seen from a mile and a half above.  This evening was special for me as it was going to be my last light over NYC for quite some time.  I was with friends, and excited for the flight, when we noticed a cloud bank encroaching on the island.  Helicopters aren't allowed to fly through cloud banks, so we were extra lucky to be able to get above the clouds to capture some truly unique images that night.
